This Halal diner is without a doubt, one of the best deals for your money in New York City.  Their falafels, lentil soup,  and other middle eastern dishes are all very good,  as is pretty much everything else on their menu.  I'm originally from Philly and tend to dismiss cheesesteak attempts in NYC, but there's is as good as I've found in the city, and a fraction of the price others sell them for.   The staff is as friendly and authentic as can be, the food is surprisingly good, the portions are large,  and with appetizers/sides starting at $1 and meals starting at $4, you just can't go wrong.  Real Brooklyn gems do still exist.

Al Noor Halal Deli is fantastic and delicious! Best Falafel in the neighborhood hands down and the best priced plates.
